you. But do you know - I - I got - I think I got - twenty-five shillings a week - then, and do you know I - I - 
I used - I used to give my mother fifteen shillings a week. Because I was the eldest and - I was the only one earning. Used to give my mother fifteen shillings a week, and I used to have to buy certain things, mind you, we had - used to have our food. The
y
 used to give us our food in those days. And - but I used to save about five shillings a week, you know, now - now - when I think of it now, I - I just can't imagine. I don't think I really went without very much, I mean, I never had any luxuries mind you
.
 But of course - we didn't expect them. I mean, we knew we couldn't have them. I mean - but of course ice cream and things like that for children wasn't known. But I tell you what I do remember as a child. That was - we used to call him Ice Cream Jack, an
d
