oint in those days, everybody had a joint you got a joint for about two shillings, you know. And - on Mondays it was always washing day, and it was a cold meat day, with mashed potatoes and pickles. Well the same thing applied, you didn't want to buy a ja
r of pickles, that was always - much more expensive, about sixpence or so, you took a basin.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347887\charrsid1069857  You could get a pennyworth of P}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 ic}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347887\charrsid1069857 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347887\charrsid1069857 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
illy, pennyworth of red cabbage or what have you. And it was enough you know, for the meal for - four or five of you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Were there any markets round here or was it all shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
Yes, there was a market, it's - it - well there - there is a - very slight remnant of it now, in what is now called Draycott Avenue. It used to be called Marlborough Road. And that was a street market
 in those days. And on a Saturday night if you went down there, 'cos the shops used to open very very late, and I - I thought it was marvellous, 'cos I was always - had to go to bad fairly early, but if - if mum hadn't got very much money at the end of th
e
 week, she'd say to me, I know what we'll do. We'll - your father can be in - with the - boys. We'll go down about ten o'clock, we'll go down to Marlborough Road and we'll probably get a joint, and do you know, I remember one Christmas when - unfortunatel
y
 we hadn't - things hadn't been very good and - I remember getting - my mother getting a turkey for half a crown. On Christmas Eve about half past ten, you know, because - you just - they just wanted to get rid of it you know sort of thing, nothing the ma
tter with it, but - it was just that - they wanted to get rid of it you know and - and we - and of course we had this turkey you know I mean, we had it all the week of course naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Would you have many people round on Christmas Day or would you go out on Christmas Day?
