ld. Well we used to go to this penny bazaar. Well I mean - for about a shilling - I mean, you - you could - festoon the tree - literally you see. Some of the things were two a penny, you see, some of the smaller things you see, and then you see, what we -
 
we did, on - on the tree would be - some - one item - particularly for each child - was there you see out of this penny bazaar. But you never reckoned to spend more than half a crown on it, well you hadn't got it so you couldn't. But - you see - people sa
y
 oh you know - children were deprived and that. They weren't, because, I mean, we - we did have - we did have something, and I mean we thought it was - it was wonderful, you know. And - and - but of course more often, you know, especially as we got - got 
older, it would be that you had some new shoes or a new - you know - frock or what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12347887\charrsid1069857 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
