x you see. Then it got to seven and then, you know, then there used to be grumbles you know, from the one that's - like, you know, one next to me, you know, oh I didn't ought to go to bed the same as the kids, you see, sort of thing. And then it got to - 
b
ut - I - I think I was always in bed about eight. I think that was about the limit you know, unless I was - and - I know I was very impressed - the first time I ever went to watch night service, I couldn't understand why everybody was out at church you kn
