w, the middle of the night, 'cos mother took me you see 'cos dad was home you see, and - of course he could - you know, I mean he was in - well the - the - children were never left you see, the - you know the youngsters were never left, you see, we were n
e
ver left you see, that is - that is the great pity at home now with children I think, you see - they - they - they've much more freedom in lots of way I mean and - and you know, - they're not so obedient probably and all that sort of thing, but you see, t
