a visit, something like that, but still it still meant money to me you see. Ah yes, ah yes, but I mean to have a doctor visit you see, you know - when you weren't what they call on the panel you know. And - and of course - we had a good laugh, 'cos he was
 
Scottish, you know, and - we had a good laugh over it and oh often afterwards he - he used to tease me and he used to say, oh well, you're my public patient you see. But I thought public sounded as if you know you didn't have to pay too much, and that sou
nded about right to me. Yes. Well - you know, it was funny what you do as kids isn't it really but still -
