\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 You said that there were other schools in this area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, my - my brother, when - of course they only took - they only took children up - boys up to seven in our sch
ool, it was really a girls school but they took little boys up to seven and - and - then he went to what they called Bowsfield school, which is still - is still going, it's a - it's - it's very - it's in the Boltons, do you know the Boltons? Yes, well it'
s
 in the Boltons and that's very modern school now, but it was in Clairville Grove in those days, it was round the corner. And - then there was - there was the Marborough, which is still there - which is quite a big school, and then there was another - ano
t
her school, also a church school, Holy Trinity, but that was in - in Sloane Street. That was at the back of Sloane Street. That's still there, that's still functions, and then of course there was for Catholic children there was the Oratory school. And the
n there was St Josephs just up the road here, oh yes, we were very - very well off for - for schools really, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did the children you went to school with come from similar homes to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Yes. Yes. It - it - yes, except that - of course round near
 us there were all these little mews places which of course - in - in the - in the very early days of course they were - they were - the coachmen, you know, they - the ladies have carriages and what have you, well then of course as they - gradually, you k
n
ow, as the time got on it got to cars you see, and they were chauffeurs - the children you see, and - you know, that - that - that made up you see, that made up the - the school - you see, that's why we had rather a floating - population as it were you se
e
 because - a lot of these children, you see, if their people - you know, they obviously had to go to the country or - go to various places you see, well sometimes they'd be away - perhaps for three months you see, perhaps people would go to Scotland or so
m
ething you see. Well children couldn't - miss school for six months you - three months at a time, so they used to have to get to - you know, I used to feel sorry for these kids you see, but they used to come back to us - when they came back to the - mews,
 
you know - you know to the London house you see. But - but most of the other children were - were people, you know, like - like myself, that lived - lived locally all the year you know and - and - and went there but - we - you know, we had quite a mixed -
 crowd of children otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Were there any gangs or things like that at the school?
