u see, so one little boy turned round and he said, well I'm going to the Home's party, 'cos he said, you always get something to bring away there, that'll be much better than going to that other party. So all the - nearly all the kids - by - boycotted the
 
other little boy whose birthday was the same day as my - I mean he had - he had his own people there and he had certain people there, but - these - these children that had been to our party, they would rather come to our party, not that we - we weren't so
 
well off as the - as the other people, you know, I mean my father - hadn't got so much as - as - as the - this other child's father had but - you see - they - they hadn't thought, I mean when - when the tea was over you'd had it, it was done, and they did
n
't play any games. You know, they just sort of sat there after the tea you know and - probably had a slice of cake you know, what have you, and - and I don't think they had such a big garden as we had where they could go out and - get off any excess you k
