Well - not very often, sometimes - some members of the family used to suddenly - remember that we belonged to them you know and used to send to us, but mostly it was
 only cards you know. But another thing I remember right from my very early - when I could - first learn to write - even if it was a card that was sent for your birthday or Christmas or anything my mother always made us write and thank, always. Always. An
d
 of course the - boys, you know, they were mostly too young to write so that - right from - right from very early age, I mean I was clobbered with writing to everybody, didn't matter who it was and if it was just a card I would write and thank them for it
,
 that was one of the things - and it's one of the few things that is done today. As a matter of fact I think - I'm one of the very few people that write loads of letters. I don't think there's a day goes by without I don't write a letter to somebody and w
h
en I write a letter I write a letter. Actually I've got airmail stationery so, you - you can guess I can - I write but - you see, nowadays - of course I suppose it's the phone and everything you know that's so easy. But, you know, I still think that there
'
s a lot - a lot to be said for getting a letter. And you know, I think if - if more people realized, you know, the - the thrill it sometimes gives older people, you now, to get letters. I'm - sure they would write more often. Oh no only older people, any 
-
 any - I think everybody more or less likes to get letters you know. Don't they, don't you think so. And - and it is more or less dying out. You know, to what it was. Of - of course, as I say, the - he postage is a bit of a - that - that's why I think tha
t
, you know, people like myself now I suppose I would spend what - three shillings a week easily on stamps, and if - when I - it - when it comes to airmails you see - quite a lot more, and I write - I write an airmail at least once a month, probably - more
 often. And probably to two or three places as well you see. Oh Christmas - Christmas time here is - is - it's - it's really lovely, I had eighty - three I think last year, and I think I had them from all corners of the world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did you have many Christmas cards when you were young?
