Yes. Well I used to, the boys used to get tuppence and the little one a penny you see. Well - dad would give sixpence each and probably give me a shilling you see. Well I would immediately -
 go to mum, you see, and I'd say, well look, you'd better have this mum, because, you know - the boys'll be wanting so and so, you know, this can go towards so and so you see, but my father would give it me to spend on myself - or expect me to spend it on
 
myself, which I didn't. But - he would expect me to, you see, he was - he was like that you see, if he had extra money everybody had to - had to sort of share it. Whereas mum would think more of the - you see, mum - my - my father was more - what shall yo
