o, or, I'm going to - or he'd come in with - with - so mum said, now - you shouldn't have - have bought all that, now - now Freda could have gone out and she would have got it much cheaper, you know. But dad wanted to do it, you see, he was like that. I t
h
ink in - you see, I'm like - it's rather funny, I'm like both my parents. In - in ways, in different ways. Of course my father always said I took after him, you know 'cos he thought - everything I did was right you know, but - in - in lots of ways I'm lik
e
 my mother you see, I mean I'm - I'm very impulsive in lots of things, I mean, I - I hope, at least I'm sure I'm not mean, I'm - I know I'm not really - but - I - I - I've got a little bit about me - that would - would say, ah, well don't - you know, don'
t
 spend the lot you know, do so and so, whereas if I was all my father I would say, oh blow the lot, you know, and then - you know, we - we'll wait for another time you see, but - I - I've got - I've got bits of each of them in me, which - which I think is
 probably quite a good thing you know, I mean -
