ther, you see, because he said - he said, it's not fair that - that - that she should - you know - she shouldn't - she should have to do, you know, all this, that and the other. So mum said, oh, well, she's the eldest, you see, and - and of course a lot o
f
 people you know like when women are talking about children and that sort of thing you know, and they said, aren't you lucky, you know, you had - most boys you see. So - mum used to rather - sort of - shake them really 'cos she used to say, well I'd rathe
r
 have had - had some more girls. And nobody apparently in those days seemed to want girls very much you see, but - of course I suppose my mother was - well I suppose, if - if - if my brother had - we'd reversed places and he'd been older, I don't know how
 we'd have got on. 'Cos - I don't think - well, in those days, yes, you see, as I say - you see - a - a girl - child, you see, wasn't expected - I mean, it wasn't - deemed necessary for them to be very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15597842\charrsid1069857 knowledgeable}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857  about anything, only about - you know, th
ings in the home and that sort of thing, whereas with the boys I mean if - if they were going to get anywhere in life I mean, well they - they just had to have the - thing, and then you see there were so many of boys things that one can't - sort of - you 
k
now - can't have a sort of a too much of a home made look I mean, you can make when they're tiny little boys, you can make little velvet trousers and - little things in that kind but of course when they get on to what they call long'uns as my brothers use
d
 to call them, you see, you can't really - very successfully, unless you're - you know, very clever, you can't tailor - a boy's suit like - like you could make - like girls things you see, so that - that quite often the boys just had to have things bought
,
 you know what I mean, that - that I just had to - you know, more or less put up with - but of course - it wasn't any hardship to me because my mother was - was quite clever and - and I mean although very often they were made out of - things of her own, I
 
mean, I don't suppose anybody would have - would have known you see because - she could - being lady - lady's maid she knew a lot about dressmaking and - and - and she could do that sort of thing, and when the boys were little it was - it was quite all ri
ght 'cos they used to wear these little - sort of - silk sort of blouses, little - little velvet knickers, and - or - or little kilts or something you know and - and - and of course they used to - always look very nice.
