. Yes. Oh yes, yes, we were very - the - the - as I say, it was - it was a very little school, it was a very ordinary little school but - I think basically we had very very good training, very good training indeed. I think so. I've never - I've never forg
o
tten the things that I learnt there anyway. And - I'm sure I - I - I was no - no worse for it, I mean I - I probably as I say if I'd have won this scholarship I'd probably have gone on and - I'd have probably - of course - you know, been able to - to lear
n
 - quite a lot more and - and - you know - probably got on very much better but - I think there's a certain amount of practical things that - that even schooling can't teach you you know, I mean - there's a lot of things one has to learn you know from - w
ell, you know, it's just everyday life isn't it, I mean, it's - just teaches you.
