No. No, we never had beer you see. Well my uncles - you know, all her people all drank you know, musicians particularly, but of course as I say, we - we used to get - uncle's beer and that sort of thing, and I thin
k my - my father was - was very good about things. The only thing my father would never do, if my uncle had had a friend in, one of his pals in which of course - called for beer - and - and the - you know, they'd gone off and the washing up was left, my f
a
ther would never wash up a beer glass. He would never wash up anything that had - had contained beer. He used to put them on one side. Wash everything else up, he - he couldn't - he couldn't bear it, but he never - he never ever said a word - to my uncle 
