Oh yes. Yes, used to be the Temperance Hall, yes. I don't think my father went there because - you see - any clubs he went to were - were c
ycling clubs you see. But - which I think a number of those - more temperate, I - I don't think - I don't think a really boozy cyclist could go very far you know. He was - he was very fond of drink, but it was - you know - lemonade - you know, the soft dr
inks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 What kind of drinks would you have with meals during the day, did you have tea or coffee or what?
