Oh, tea, tea chiefly, tea - oh wonderful tea drinkers, all - you know, all - all the family. Coffee wasn't - there - there wasn't such a - you
 see, coffee is a thing that's come on this last twenty - odd years, you know, for English people really. My mother - my mother loved coffee, because - you see, she'd lived so long abroad you see and - various times that she was so used to it you see. I -
 the only time I got used to coffee was - of course when I was in France because you see - they - they hardly ever had tea, it was - it was far too expensive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 When did you first go to France?
