\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 What did you call this woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh Tilly. I never knew what her really name was. Tilly something I suppose you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 How did you get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh all right, well I just - I just used to - didn't used to both
er - I - I just used to do the same thing, I used to - give her a cup of tea when she come in which was the usual thing and I used to go - round to the pub or - if it - you know - if - if - if it had stopped in that time I used to go to the off license wh
i
ch was next to the pub and get a bottle of beer, I used to get a quart bottle you see, and put the - put it down beside her and I used to make her - fairly hefty sandwiches of bread and cheese you see, and then I used to leave her to do - you know, she us
ed to do all the whites and then all the coloureds and what have you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 How many hours did she come in for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh she'd come in for the day. Oh used to work for the day in that - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 What did she call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh she called me by my name. Y
ou see. And - oh she got used to me you know, and then I used to say to her - when we were having our dinner, well dinner's ready you see, and then I used to - you know, get up this dinner and she often used to say, oh this is jolly nice, you know. And - 
I
 used to say, well, yes, dad started it and I finished it off, you know. So she said, well it's very nice you know and - she used to have a - you know, a good - good meal you know. And then - I used to say to her, well - you - you needn't go back yet, 'co
s
 I'd heard my mother say this, you can have a rest if you like, you know. But I don't think she could read or write see so - I used to get the - she used to like titbits out the local paper, so I used to pick up the local paper and read her out all the go
s
sip, you know, in the local paper you know, she said, oh fancy, you know, 'cos generally there was somebody in there that - that she knew about, you know, she knew about them, and she used to say, oh I do enjoy coming here. She used to to go to lots of pe
o
ples, you know, various days you know. But - she said, I do enjoy coming here. And then she used to say sometimes, used to say - she said, it's a good job - good - good job - good job your mother didn't have boys first of all isn't it, see, so I said, oh 
I don't know. So I said, I suppose they'd have done the same. So she said, no fear. I - I never ever knew whether she was ever a Miss anybody or a Mrs or what she was, she was a - it was a sort of a non-descript type of person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did she come from around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
Oh yes, she lived - around about, but nobody seemed to know very much about her but - if anybody wanted anything I think she acted as sort of midwife and - done all sorts of jobs you know, well old I'm calling her, I suppose she was
 about sixty which of course was - you know, terribly old to me you know, but I mean she was older than - my mother was at the time you know. And - I suppose I thought she was old you know. And she seemed to be old lady, but she had plenty of go in her an
d
 I mean she - you know, she was able to do all this and then she'd - oh - oh I think she used to sometimes come back - at the end of the week sometimes to do a bit of ironing. You see, 'cos I - I - I - I - I think she used to, especially if there were she
ets and things like that because - I think she used to come back - but I don't think she did a whole day then, I think she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did you say you had your uncle living there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Yes. Yes. Yes. My mother's youngest brother, yes. He died when he was forty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 How many years would he live with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
Oh several years. Several years, right - and - during - that's what I say, I - I was very lucky really because - as I say, as far as - you know, anything to do with music you see used to say, 
oh look uncle, I've got - I've got to learn this song for school. And he used to say, oh all right, well come up in the parlour. And I used to go up and of course he used to - he wasn't a pianist, but he - he could play of course and he used to play throu
g
h the notes you see and so then I used to sort of - like follow him you know, then he used to say, no, that's not right, that's not a G that's so and so you know, then he used to make me - like go over it to do it properly you see, so that of course at th
e - you know - after two or three days I mean I - I mean, I - I I really knew the - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Would he eat with you as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh yes. Oh yes, when he was in. But of course you see, it all depended how he worked you see, if he had matinees, of cour
se he'd - he'd get up - 'cos he mostly got up late because, you see, if it was evening jobs he - he wasn't home 'til about nearly midnight But it always used to be so - so strange to me, because he always used to eat quite a big supper - at night you see,
 
and - we didn't have - well we didn't have suppers us children, we had just a glass of milk and - you know, cake, but - I don't think mum and dad had - I don't think they had their meal late at night like that you see, but you see, it's what they're - wha
t
 - what he was used to you see, and then in the morning, first thing he'd have a cup of tea which dad would - probably take him in and then, about eleven o'clock, he'd have his breakfast you see. Which of course was - you know, you see - unless of course 
h
e was going to a matinee or anything like that you see. If he - if he'd got a matinee - which he'd got to get to whatever theatre it was you see, he'd - he'd have to have - he - he'd - he'd get up a bit earlier, have a breakfast, and then he'd have a sort
 of a - what you call a snack you see, buthe'd still have his meal at - proper meal at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 But the rest of the family, when they were all there, had regular eating times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh yes. Oh regular times, yes. Well that had to be because of school for us children you know and that sort of thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Can you remember whether you were ever allowed to talk during meals in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Well, not too much, no, no, no. But we - we - we were told not to stretch and grab for things you know, we 
had to - ask for things to be passed you see, and I think that's where my mother started - started on us, trying to din a little bit of French into us you see. You had - have to say, voulez vous passez, you know - so on, you see, that's how we knew all th
e
 - all the sort of eatables and - and things like that and - tasse de tea, you know, you knew - you knew a cup and - things of that kind you know, little things like that, but I mean - as regards, I mean, I never - I never learnt French as to know - you k
now - how to speak properly like verbs and what have you you know. But I think I could - I could - get on - all right if somebody was - you know, was - you know, I mean I could make myself understood quite well you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 So you had a smattering of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Yes, a little bit - a little bit of it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 When your mother was there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15597842\charrsid1069857 can you remember her having les}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 s food so the rest of you could have more, anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Well - I think that would be the case when we were very hard up. Yes
, very hard up, and - I - I can remember - myself - you know, when I could see the little ones looking, you know, that often I wouldn't have a - another piece of another - one, even if I could have eaten it, if I thought there wasn't, you know, that - I -
 I've done that, but I've never - I've never really - I mean I - I - I've never starved. I've never starved. I - I've gone - gone - well - sometimes I - I could have fe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15597842\charrsid1069857 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 t I could have had a little bit more you know but I knew it wasn't there and I couldn't have it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 If there was enough were you allowed to have second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh yes. Oh yes, if there was enough, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 What about their attitude towards things that were left uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh well that was considered ver
y bad, unless for some reason it was something that you really - from a digestive point of view, you couldn't tackle you know. And - and then - then of course it was - but otherwise I mean it was that or you had no - whatever followed, pudding or what hav
e you, you see. You finished it up. Oh yes, you weren't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did your father have more than anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
No. No. Oh no, no. No. And 'course he was - he was marvellous for - for carving when he had a - 'cos I - I don't know if you know but - he was h
ead carver before he - he took on the - chef's work, and of course they have to get so many slices out of a - out of the joint you see, and - and of course he - I mean, he could do it to perfection, you know, I mean - and I mean, when you - the - there's 
-
 there's a certain art in - in having a - whatever joint it is you see, it's a certain way that you can carve and of course if - if you're in the hotel or catering business I mean you - you've got to get - you know, to the best advantage, and then you've 
g
ot to see that, if it's pork or a fat joint or anything of that, I mean you've got to see that a - a fair proportion of the fat is delivered with the - with the other, but you've got to do it in such a way that - you know, somebody doesn't immediately loo
k
 and say, oh I've got all the so and so fat, you see. You see, there's - there's a way, there's an art of doing it, I used to love to watch my father - used to interest me, you know, this - this knife he kept you know, with the long blade you know and I u
sed to see it sizzling through you know, oh I'd love to be able to do that you know. No, my mother never ever - never ever carved the joint you see, but - not when dad was home anyway you know because - that was -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Who would serve the meal up, would it be your father again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
No, mum would do every - he - he would - he would do the meat, you know, I mean if we were all there together he would - he - that - that was his part, then he'd - had - you know, he'd - he'd put - he'd put it all out on the pl
ates, and of course he knew exactly what we - what we children would have, you see. But now and again mum would say to him, oh no, he - he can eat a bit of fat. Put a bit of fat there or - you know, put a bit - you know, 'cos - he'd say, oh well I don't t
h
ink he - he likes that, so mum said, oh well - a little bit won't hurt, you know, he'd have - dad would have been more lenient with us I think you know. But - then see dad didn't have to do with us all the time did he, you see. But of course mum was proba
b
ly right because I mean - she wouldn't have - made us eat a heap of fat or anything like that you know but - you know, my - dad would - you know, if you sort of looked and went; you know - sort of looked at him you know he'd sort of - he'd sort of - 'cour
se -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Where would the little ones sit when they were too young to sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh well, we always had a high chair, somebody was always in the high chair you see and always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Who would feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Well I would. Usually. Very quickly
 how they - how they got on to ordinary food too I tell you but of course I used to have to do a lot of cutting up in the - well of course mum used to mostly do that, you know, she used to - dad used to give her the plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did you have a set order of being served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
No, not that I remember, no, I don't think so. Dad used to probably sit down when he'd done the carving and - you know, then either mum would put the vegetables on or more likely he'd do it himself and - he'd start away, you know, bu
t - us children used to - used to wait 'til - you know, mum or dad had started before we, you know, used to start. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Were you taught to use your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh yes. Yes? Yes, we were taught you know as soon as we wer
e - able to do it, of course the - tiny ones used to have a - spoon I think when they were very very young they had a sort of pusher thing you know which - you know I used to sort of - try - try them with first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Could you bring toys to the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
No, I don't think that was - only in - must have been very early stages, no, I think that was rather frowned on, although we had quite a big table you know, but - I don't think that was - no, because I mean - the - the business of having your food was -
 you know, was a business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did anyone say grace at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
At one time I think we used to say grace, yes. Now how did that come about? I think we used to - we used to sort of say a bit of - you know - say a few words, for what we are about to receive, or something you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Were you ever taught to pray?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
Oh used to always say our prayers, I used to listen to the prayers, oh yes. 'Cos they used to get very funny at times you know, children used to - of course naturally - put in for al
l what they wanted you know and of course it always used to - God bless mummy, God bless daddy, and then - all of a sudden they used to look at me and then they used to put me in, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Were there any family prayers or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 You say that the only musical instrument was a piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Yes. More or less always had a piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did your parents play many games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Well - don't know that they played very - I mean, dad would - would - would play when 
he was in, he would - he would play with 'em, I mean - mostly dad's - dad's thing was, you know, when toys got broken you know, mend this dad, mend this, and then of course he'd mend it. And then he'd - he'd probably, if it was a - truck thing or somethin
g
 on wheels you know, and then he'd say, now let's see how this goes, well then in the end you'd probably find dad on the floor with the - whichever child it was you know, and then mum'd come in, she said, oh, you know, can't have all this bunkum you know,
 and then of course they'd go - probably go out in the - in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Would you play in the parlour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh no. Oh no, certainly not, no, in the - in the kitchen, the kitchen was our room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 When you had your meals could you just get down when you felt like it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh no, no, you waited, you waited, then you were told, you know, when you could get down, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 What did your parents do to amuse themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh I don't know, I think they used to do - well they - they - they both lik
ed reading and of course mum used - was generally busy doing some sort of mending or - or needlework of some sort, you know. And - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did they have many friends round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Not a great deal. No, not a great deal. Not that they weren't - friendly 
people, but you know I suppose the circumstances didn't - didn't warrant it, either they were people with - you know, several children or - or what have you and - you know, didn't come out, and of course I think not - not being drinkers you know is - is o
n
e of the things, but - I do remember round about Christmastime and - you know, Boxing Day and various times like that - there - there used to be quite a few people in playing cards and that sort of thing and, you know, mum an I used to make the sandwiches
 and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 What would they think about playing cards or something like that on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh they wouldn't do it. It wouldn't be necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did they ever have neighbours round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Not very much, no, my mother wasn't - wasn't a - I mean she was
 a friendly enough person and I mean, you know, in the street and that sort of thing, but - she didn't like the idea of neighbours coming round, you know, she always thought, well - it generally ends up in a row of some sort you know. No, she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Who would be the people who came round, would they be relatives or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Well, relatives and odd friends probably that mum - know mum in the - in the past and - and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did your mother and father have the same friends or did your father have his friends and your mother have her friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
Well, they - they mostly - mostly both knew, you know, whatever friends came round, you know. No, they weren't - they weren't people for - for going out and - they - they very seldom went out toget
her because as I say their pursuits were - were so different, wasn't because they - they were quarrelling or anything, it's just that - you see, mum and I weren't - very interested in - and, you know, when we got older I know once - on one occasion dad sa
id, oh, he said, you know, they keep on at the club asking me about you - I suppose dead talked about us you see, well this was in latter years you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 So really they'd have their own different interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Had their own pursuits you see, yes, and - and it worked very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did you tell me your mother was making records before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh yes. Oh yes, long before. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 So she'd be going out when she was free?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Yes, yes, she used to - but - but she did have a re
cording trumpet in - in one house where we were, you know, that - she used to be able to record on you know, on the old wax - cylinder things you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 She actually could record in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh yes. Oh yes. Well I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Not just a record player playing it back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 No. Oh no, no, no, weren't - weren't record players in those days, I mean - yes, it was a - a phonograph that they had, yes. But she -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 You could actually make your own records?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Yes you could, yes, you could make them. We
ll then I think you had to take them, these wax things to the company, I don't know what they did to them, I don't know - no, it was His Master's Voice mostly. She -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did she ever have anybody round for singing evenings or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 She'd always go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
No, well of course we - we - you know, she was in - very big choirs and things like that you know where she did oratorio and that sort of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Would she ever go on tours with these choirs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh yes. Y
es? She went with the Fleet Street choir, she went to - she went what they call the Scandinavian tours, she went for six weeks, she went to - Norway, Holland and Sweden. Yes. I wasn't able to go, I was - I was very upset, I would love to have gone, but I 
c
ouldn't - I couldn't spare six weeks of - you see, and - and firms and anybody weren't - weren't even lenient in those days to ever let you have it if you paid your own - time off, they wouldn't let you have that amount of timeoff in those days you know, 
I mean, it's different now if you go through for anything, they - they let you do it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 You say your father was interested in cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Well, it was a way life nearly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Were you ever interested in sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 No, not really. No, not re
ally - 'cos I - I wasn't very strong as a child, I used to have terrible fainting fits you see and I wasn't - and I - I was never allowed to do what they call physical exercise, I wasn't allowed to do it, because I used to faint you see, I - I'm very very
 sorry about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did you have many hobbies when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
Don't know that I had really very many hobbies, I think, you know - the children and - and various things, shopping and - and looking after - you know, I - I - I don't think I had much time for hobbies really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did you do anything like fishing or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 No. No, I didn't, my brothers used to like fishing and - 'course they liked cricket and football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Yes, we normally had a cat - always
, and - at various stages we had a dog. You know, that - we had, and I think my brothers tried at various times to bring - you know, other things into the - into the place, I - I know - one of them, when he used to - want a fight and he had a pet mouse an
d he used to try and put this down my - back and - you know, frighten the life out of me and - that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did you ever play with other girls or neighbours children or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did I? Oh I used to have girl friends, yes. But - I mean - I
 didn't - I didn't see a lot of them, you see, they were - they were more fortunate than I was, you see, because - they - they mostly had either older sisters or older brothers or - they were in the middle of the family and - when they'd finished school a
n
d had their tea and what have you and probably do an errand or so for their mother - I mean, they - they could go off somewhere, well, it was very seldom I could go off, the only times I could go off was when I went to - Girls Friendly Society you know - 
and that sort of thing and saw them there. Then come back you see. But I never sort of went off very much on my own you know with - with other girls, not until I was -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did you ever play in neighbours houses or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Not very much, 
no. No. No, well you see most of the neighbours were like ourselves only most of them had more children than us, most had seven or eight children you see, and - I suppose - they - you know there were plenty to - in themselves you see and if - if each of t
hat child - each - each of - if you had a family of eight and each of the children had - friends, well you - you - you soon got a - a family up didn't you, you soon got a - crowd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Was there any one particular brother that you felt closer to than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
Well - the one that's alive now, he was terribly delicate. Terrible delicate, we had a lot of trouble with him, he - he'd had - by the time he was twelve he'd had fourteen operations, he had - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15597842\charrsid1069857 abscess}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857  on the brain, neu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15597842\charrsid1069857 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
itis media, it - it's - i
t's - it's a wonder really he's turned out very clever actually. But it's a wonder because - it's - it's a very terrifying thing you know and it's so near the brain that it - it could - you know, it could cause madness you see. It's a very - but I think i
t was a result of a fall, actually you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 So he was in hospital quite a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
Oh yes, he was in hospital for - oh - I - I think he only had about three years of schooling, but - he ended up on the - top class. No, he'd - we - he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 How did you cope for paying for hospitals in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
Oh yes didn't pay. You didn't pay. But - you had a - you know, you had a lot of - toing and froing, there wasn't the - as I remember there wasn't the ambulance system - very prevalent in those days, I 
mean, if you went on an ambulance you know, you - you - you'd gone, you know, it was the last straw sort of thing. Oh and there - there wasn't so many facilities and of course - I'm talking of the - where he mostly went, where I remember going with mother
 with him, was - to the Tap Street, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15597842\charrsid1069857 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857  children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15597842\charrsid1069857 
\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
s hospital which is now - only just now, I only saw it - about a fortnight ago, it's - it's made into a - a sort of a convent place, the old Tap Street hospital. But then you see, as he got older - as he pa
ssed fourteen, they wouldn't attend him any longer as a child you see, and he had to go to Charing Cross after that. You know, and have - and you see, I always used to have to go with mother because you see there was always one or two children to take you
 see and of course - with him, you know, he - he - obviously had to have various things done - you know, and - and of course mother could only cope with him so I had to go to mind the other babies you see, when they go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Can you remember a funeral in the family in these years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
Only my grandma's, my mother's mother. But - we children didn't go. And of course I remember my little brother, the one little brother, I don't remember the other - one that died, but I remember the one - one, you know, the o
ne that had the accident and I did go of course to his funeral because - you know, for a long time I - I - I couldn't realize that he was - he was dead at all you know, it was - it was a great blow. They thought they were going to have a lot of trouble wi
t
h me actually because - I think I was so near him, you know, that - you know, it was just one of the things that I couldn't - couldn't imagine you see. You see, he - he had an accident you see and he lived for about six months on his - 'cos he had a wonde
r
ful constitution, but - he died from meningitis. Meningitis of the spine you see, and it didn't really come out - until after death, the actual, you know, markings you see. But it was a - it was a great - it was a great shock to me, I was a long long time
 before I could - sort of get over it you know. Oh -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did people draw the curtains and things like that in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh yes. And of course another thing I can remember which a lot of people don't remember, when people were very ill in those day
s - they always put straw down outside - in the road you know because - well, there were mostly - a lot of horse traffic of course in those days too, but - they put the straw down, that was when people were very ill, I mean, better off people than us of c
o
urse that could afford it, I don't know - I suppose they - did it to the council or something you know, and they used to put the - these bales of straw down so that - and of course us kids thought it was great, you know, we used to shuffle through it you 
know, but - it was done, you know, to - to keep the noise down as much as possible, but that was mostly for people that - that were nursed at home. Probably had - heart trouble or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Were you ever taken out shopping with your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, quite often. We used to go down to Berwick market sometimes for - for a change of sc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15597842\charrsid1069857 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 nery you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Was this in Pi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15597842\charrsid1069857 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 cadilly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Off - off there, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 No, I don't thin
k very often, I - I don't think there was many occasions when we could have done really you see, it was - it was rather - rather difficult, well when we did as I say we mostly went for the day, and then - like we'd all go, you know, as - as - he'd go firs
t of all with the - on the bike you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 You say you never actually went away for a holiday, it used to be more day trips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14232920 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 Not very often. Once or twice I did because we had - my mother had a sister who in the Isle of Wight, and we used to go th
ere sometimes, you know, for a holiday. And then in turn we'd have her children would come up - to us in London you see. I went about far more with - with my cousins and people like that, showing them round London than - ever I did on my own you know beca
use - when they come up from various - parts of the country they wanted to see all around you see, so of course I used to be - have to be the one to take them you know. Go to Madame Taussaud}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15597842\charrsid1069857 
\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 s you know and what have you. Like when this - one that was here a
 little while ago, when they came from India you see, there were four - four of the - my uncle's - children, and - this Spanish mother of theirs, and - we more or less - sort of took them in 'til they could get somewhere - to live you see, but of course t
h
ey were a very different cup of tea from - from us children you see, they - they - they'd lived in India for so long, they'd had native servants, they'd - they'd more or less run wild you see, and - they - they - they weren't used to discipline at all, an
d
 - oh they - you know, I think - I think it - went down very badly first of all with them but of course - mother wouldn't - wouldn't let them - you know, wouldn't - let them sort of get her down, I mean she said, oh well, you're here and I'm looking after
 
you, you know, well, their mother was in hospital here, and - you - you'll have to - do what we do, you know. I think they used to feel sorry for us actually. But - afterwards since he's grown up I mean he's realized you know, you know, how - how good - y
o
u know - it was really for them really but of course - - it was really a bit unfair I suppose coming - coming - all the way from India you see and then - this Spanish mother of theirs you see, she wasn't - wasn't - probably hadn't got the same ideas as us
 
- about how children should be you see and of course as - as you say in - in those days I mean servants were - you know, very very cheap - out there. And you see, and - and they weren't used - and then uncle you see was away a lot - you know, and - very o
f
ten they used to have to go - whatever part of India they were if it got too hot they used to go up in the hills and that sort of thing, the wives and children you know. So that - you know, they - they never really had much discipline you see and she wasn
'
t - she - she - she was a - she was a very sweet woman as a person in herself but she - she was no - there was no question of - discipline at all, I mean that didn't come into it, I mean the children cried for what they wanted and they got it and I mean t
hat was it you see, but of course that didn't go down with my mother, I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15597842\charrsid1069857  mean - you know, that was no g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2569466\charrsid1069857 
o, you - you - you didn't cry unless you were hurt or something was wrong, you didn't cry for - just that you - you wanted something and - you know, and - 
and of course, food everything was different to them you see, but of course they had to get used to what - you know, what - what we had and - and that's and that sort of thing.
